Third-Party Acknowledgments:

This software implements algorithms and techniques from various sources:

1. Levenshtein Distance Algorithm
   - Public domain algorithm for computing edit distance
   - Reference: Vladimir Levenshtein (1965)

2. Damerau-Levenshtein Distance Algorithm  
   - Extension of Levenshtein distance including transpositions
   - Reference: Frederick J. Damerau (1964)

3. Soundex Algorithm (Modified)
   - Phonetic algorithm for matching similar-sounding words
   - Public domain algorithm developed by Robert C. Russell and Margaret K. Odell

4. Trie Data Structure
   - Standard computer science data structure for prefix matching
   - Public domain implementation

All algorithms have been implemented from scratch based on published academic
papers and are not derived from any copyrighted code.

================================================================================

Dictionary Data:

The included English dictionary (dictionaries/en_US.dict) contains common 
English words and their frequencies. This word list is compiled from public 
domain sources and is provided for testing and demonstration purposes.

For production use, consider using more comprehensive dictionaries such as:
- Hunspell dictionaries (LGPL/GPL licensed)
- SCOWL (Spell Checker Oriented Word Lists) - public domain
- WordNet database - WordNet License

